# Task 2: Real-Life Mapping

## Selected Example: College Admission System

| Salesforce Object | Real-Life Mapping |
|------------------|------------------|
| Account | College |
| Contact | Student |
| Lead | Student interested in admission |
| Opportunity | Admission application process |

---

## Explanation

### Account = College
The college or institution providing education services.

---

### Contact = Student
The student who is connected to the college.

---

### Lead = Student Interested in Admission
A student who asks for course details or admission information but has not yet enrolled.

---

### Opportunity = Admission Application Process
The active admission process where the college and student are working toward successful enrollment.

---

# Conclusion

Salesforce CRM helps organizations manage relationships and track processes efficiently using Leads, Contacts, Opportunities, and Accounts.
